Wrapper Types


Boolean b1 = Boolean.valueOf("tRuE");  //true
Boolean b2 = Boolean.valueOf("fAlSe"); //false
Boolean b3 = Boolean.valueOf("abc");   //false
Boolean b4 = null;					   //null
System.out.println(b1 + ":" + b2 + ":" + b3 + ":" + b4);

Boolean.valueOf(String) method uses equalsIgnoreCase method to validate the passed String, so if passed String is "true" ('t', 'r', 'u' and 'e' can be in any case), then boolean value stored in Boolean object is true otherwise false.




